name: Revolver
description: Homage to Revolver, my favourite album by the Beatles, which was released in 1966. The original cover was made by Klaus Voormann, who was chosen by the band. He was paid only £50 for his work but he suggested he would have been happy to do it for free. I was paid exactly the same amount when I designed my first album cover in 2001 for Charles Webster’s Born on the 24th of July.
